jobInfo.postDescription:
Responsibilities:

	Develop testing programs based on National Instruments LabVIEW and TestStand for automotive product (ECU), Infotainment system and consumer product.
	Work with Mechanic engineer and Hardware engineer to define the test system. 
	Work with customer to define the test solution. 
	Onsite debugging and troubleshooting based on design documentation.
	Domestic and international Travelling for other project support.

Education:
	College degree or bachelor degree or above, major in Computer science, software engineering, Electrical engineering or related

Knowledge/Languages:
	LabVIEW
	TestStand
	Knowledge and understanding schematic of test and control system (analog and digital circuit)
	Better English level, written, Read, oral and understood.

Qualification Requirements:
	3-10 years of software experience at test development or control systems development.
	Very good application experience on test related tools (LabVIEW\C#), TestStand is a nice to have capability.
	Familiar with buses (Serial, GPIB, RS232, CAN, LIN, K-line), experience with FPGA design will be preferred.
	Have experience using NI DIO\DAQ, and have system concept for NI test platform
	1 or 2 years’ experience at Automotive Electronics Manufacturing will be preferred.
	strong analytical skills with ability to troubleshooting and work independently and effectively
